{"pageProps":{"data":{"id":112991,"date":"2021-03-30T10:30:51","date_gmt":"2021-03-30T14:30:51","guid":{"rendered":"https://blog.ted.com/?p=112991"},"modified":"2021-04-02T16:56:24","modified_gmt":"2021-04-02T20:56:24","slug":"meet-the-2021-class-of-ted-fellows","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https://blog.ted.com/meet-the-2021-class-of-ted-fellows/","title":{"rendered":"Meet the 2021 class of TED Fellows"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-113005\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED015-TED-2021_TED-Blog-870x653-01.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"900\" height=\"676\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED015-TED-2021_TED-Blog-870x653-01.png 3626w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED015-TED-2021_TED-Blog-870x653-01.png?resize=150,113 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED015-TED-2021_TED-Blog-870x653-01.png?resize=250,188 250w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED015-TED-2021_TED-Blog-870x653-01.png?resize=768,577 768w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED015-TED-2021_TED-Blog-870x653-01.png?resize=530,398 530w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED015-TED-2021_TED-Blog-870x653-01.png?resize=1536,1153 1536w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED015-TED-2021_TED-Blog-870x653-01.png?resize=2048,1537 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The <a href=\"https://www.ted.com/participate/ted-fellows-program\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">TED Fellows program</a> is thrilled to announce the 2021 cohort of TED Fellows, whose work spans five continents and represents 14 countries &#8212; including, for the first time, Peru. Each TED Fellow was selected for their remarkable achievements, the potential impact of their work and their commitment to community building.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">This year&#8217;s TED Fellows include a dermatologist teaching doctors how to better serve their patients with darker skin, the inventor of a hybrid-electric aircraft and a honey entrepreneur using beekeeping to mitigate human-elephant conflict. Also, a sex educator transforming the way we talk about pleasure, a climate-impact journalist and a playwright whose work is slated to be one of the very first new shows on Broadway when theaters reopen &#8212; to name just a few. </span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">The TED Fellows program celebrates its twelfth year with a network of 512 Fellows from 100 countries.</span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113013 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Rumaitha_Al_Busaidi_2021_Fellow-1-e1617050993433.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Rumaitha_Al_Busaidi_2021_Fellow-1-e1617050993433.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Rumaitha_Al_Busaidi_2021_Fellow-1-e1617050993433.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Rumaitha_Al_Busaidi_2021_Fellow-1-e1617050993433.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Rumaitha_Al_Busaidi_2021_Fellow-1-e1617050993433.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Rumaitha_Al_Busaidi_2021_Fellow-1-e1617050993433.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Rumaitha_Al_Busaidi_2021_Fellow-1-e1617050993433.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Rumaitha_Al_Busaidi_2021_Fellow-1-e1617050993433.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /></p>\n<p><strong><br />\nRumaitha Al Busaidi</strong><br />\n<em>Adventurer + entrepreneur | Oman<br />\n</em>Scientist, activist and athlete empowering Arab women to step into spaces previously denied to them &#8212; whether it&#8217;s a football field, volcano summit or the front line of the battle against climate change. Rumaitha Al Busaidi is the founder of WomeX, a platform teaching negotiation skills to Arab women in order to nurture a new wave of female entrepreneurs in the region.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113014 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Alicia_Chong_2021_Fellow-e1617051080109.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Alicia_Chong_2021_Fellow-e1617051080109.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Alicia_Chong_2021_Fellow-e1617051080109.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Alicia_Chong_2021_Fellow-e1617051080109.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Alicia_Chong_2021_Fellow-e1617051080109.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Alicia_Chong_2021_Fellow-e1617051080109.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Alicia_Chong_2021_Fellow-e1617051080109.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Alicia_Chong_2021_Fellow-e1617051080109.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /><br />\n<strong>Alicia Chong Rodriguez</strong><br />\n<em>Health care technology entrepreneur | Costa Rica + Peru<br />\n</em>Engineer and founder of Bloomer Tech, a company transforming everyday bras into smart medical devices that gather often overlooked data on heart disease in women, a frequently misdiagnosed and under-researched killer.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_113060\" style=\"width: 910px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-113060\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-full wp-image-113060\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_10-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"900\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_10-1.jpg 5184w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_10-1.jpg?resize=150,100 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_10-1.jpg?resize=250,167 250w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_10-1.jpg?resize=768,512 768w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_10-1.jpg?resize=530,353 530w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_10-1.jpg?resize=1536,1024 1536w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_10-1.jpg?resize=2048,1365 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-113060\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Image from <em>To Catch a Dream</em>, a surreal fashion film directed by Jim Chuchu.</p></div>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113017 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_2021_Fellow-e1617051140640.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_2021_Fellow-e1617051140640.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_2021_Fellow-e1617051140640.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_2021_Fellow-e1617051140640.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_2021_Fellow-e1617051140640.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_2021_Fellow-e1617051140640.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_2021_Fellow-e1617051140640.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jim_Chuchu_2021_Fellow-e1617051140640.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /><br />\n<strong>Jim Chuchu</strong><br />\n<em>Filmmaker + cultural innovator | Kenya</em><br />\nFilmmaker and founder of The Nest Collective, a Nairobi-based artist group. Jim Chuchu’s film <em>Stories of Our Lives</em> celebrates the narratives of Kenya&#8217;s queer community in the midst of pervasive societal censure. He is also founder of the HEVA Fund, the first organization in the region dedicated to making capital investments in the creative sector and building financial infrastructure around creative pursuits in East Africa.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_113042\" style=\"width: 910px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-113042\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"wp-image-113042 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/HawaiiCoastSelfie.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"900\" height=\"506\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/HawaiiCoastSelfie.jpg 3552w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/HawaiiCoastSelfie.jpg?resize=150,84 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/HawaiiCoastSelfie.jpg?resize=250,141 250w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/HawaiiCoastSelfie.jpg?resize=768,432 768w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/HawaiiCoastSelfie.jpg?resize=530,298 530w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/HawaiiCoastSelfie.jpg?resize=1536,864 1536w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/HawaiiCoastSelfie.jpg?resize=2048,1152 2048w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/HawaiiCoastSelfie.jpg?resize=283,160 283w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/HawaiiCoastSelfie.jpg?resize=185,104 185w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/HawaiiCoastSelfie.jpg?resize=73,42 73w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-113042\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">By retrofitting existing aircraft with a hybrid-electric system, mechanical engineer Cory Combs is building the biggest plane ever to fly with hybrid propulsion: the Electric EEL.</p></div>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113019 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Cory_Combs_2021_Fellow-e1617051194472.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Cory_Combs_2021_Fellow-e1617051194472.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Cory_Combs_2021_Fellow-e1617051194472.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Cory_Combs_2021_Fellow-e1617051194472.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Cory_Combs_2021_Fellow-e1617051194472.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Cory_Combs_2021_Fellow-e1617051194472.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Cory_Combs_2021_Fellow-e1617051194472.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Cory_Combs_2021_Fellow-e1617051194472.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /><br />\n<strong>Cory Combs</strong><br />\n<em>Electric aviation entrepreneur | US</em><br />\nCofounder of Ampaire, a startup developing the next generation of hybrid-electric aircraft to reduce the environmental impact of air travel. Their Electric EEL is the largest hybrid-electric aircraft ever to fly &#8212; and the first to have flown a jaw-dropping 341-mile route.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113020 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Farwiza_Farhan_2021_Fellow-e1617051230857.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Farwiza_Farhan_2021_Fellow-e1617051230857.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Farwiza_Farhan_2021_Fellow-e1617051230857.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Farwiza_Farhan_2021_Fellow-e1617051230857.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Farwiza_Farhan_2021_Fellow-e1617051230857.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Farwiza_Farhan_2021_Fellow-e1617051230857.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Farwiza_Farhan_2021_Fellow-e1617051230857.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Farwiza_Farhan_2021_Fellow-e1617051230857.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /><br />\n<strong>Farwiza Farhan</strong><br />\n<em>Conservationist | Indonesia</em><br />\nFounder of HAkA, an organization working to protect the Leuser Ecosystem in Sumatra &#8212; a UNESCO world heritage site and the last place on Earth where the endangered orangutan, rhino, elephant and tiger still roam together in the wild. Farwiza Farhan is strengthening the power of women and grassroots community in the Leuser Ecosystem to meaningfully participate in environmental protection, conservation and decision-making.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113021 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Larry_Irvin_2021_Fellow-e1617051286724.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Larry_Irvin_2021_Fellow-e1617051286724.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Larry_Irvin_2021_Fellow-e1617051286724.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Larry_Irvin_2021_Fellow-e1617051286724.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Larry_Irvin_2021_Fellow-e1617051286724.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Larry_Irvin_2021_Fellow-e1617051286724.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Larry_Irvin_2021_Fellow-e1617051286724.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Larry_Irvin_2021_Fellow-e1617051286724.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /></p>\n<p><strong style=\"font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen-Sans, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;\"><br />\nLarry Irvin</strong><br />\n<em>Education innovator | US</em><br />\nFounder of Brothers Empowered to Teach (BE2T), an organization recruiting and training men of color to become teachers. Through innovative programming, mentorship and paid fellowships, BE2T is increasing the number of Black male teachers in US public schools.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_113043\" style=\"width: 910px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-113043\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-full wp-image-113043\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna-Lester-UCSF_20190522_Lester_044.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"900\" height=\"601\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna-Lester-UCSF_20190522_Lester_044.jpg 3500w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna-Lester-UCSF_20190522_Lester_044.jpg?resize=150,100 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna-Lester-UCSF_20190522_Lester_044.jpg?resize=250,167 250w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna-Lester-UCSF_20190522_Lester_044.jpg?resize=768,513 768w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna-Lester-UCSF_20190522_Lester_044.jpg?resize=530,354 530w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna-Lester-UCSF_20190522_Lester_044.jpg?resize=1536,1025 1536w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna-Lester-UCSF_20190522_Lester_044.jpg?resize=2048,1367 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-113043\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Jenna Lester works with a patient at the Skin of Color dermatology program at UCSF. Lester founded the program to address the underrepresentation of non-white skin in dermatology research and practice. (Photo: Barbara Ries / UCSF)</p></div>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113022 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna_Lester_2021_Fellow-e1617051373593.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna_Lester_2021_Fellow-e1617051373593.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna_Lester_2021_Fellow-e1617051373593.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna_Lester_2021_Fellow-e1617051373593.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna_Lester_2021_Fellow-e1617051373593.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna_Lester_2021_Fellow-e1617051373593.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna_Lester_2021_Fellow-e1617051373593.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Jenna_Lester_2021_Fellow-e1617051373593.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /><br />\n<strong>Jenna C. Lester</strong><br />\n<em>Dermatologist | US</em><br />\nFounder of Skin of Color dermatology program at UCSF, which is addressing the persistent issues that arise from the exclusion and marginalization of non-white patients in medical research and practice. Jenna Lester is combatting medical disparities due to racial inequality, addressing vital education gaps in textbooks and curriculum about non-white skin and training a new generation of doctors.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113024 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Lei_Li_2021_Fellow-e1617051455833.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Lei_Li_2021_Fellow-e1617051455833.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Lei_Li_2021_Fellow-e1617051455833.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Lei_Li_2021_Fellow-e1617051455833.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Lei_Li_2021_Fellow-e1617051455833.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Lei_Li_2021_Fellow-e1617051455833.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Lei_Li_2021_Fellow-e1617051455833.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Lei_Li_2021_Fellow-e1617051455833.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /><br />\n<strong>Lei Li</strong><br />\n<em>Medical imaging innovator | China + US</em><br />\nEngineer developing advanced photoacoustic imaging that can track the progress of diseases, such as cancer, that can otherwise go undetected. This process (which is much safer than other forms of radiation-based imaging) produces high-resolution images of our deepest internal systems, providing anatomical, functional and molecular information all at once.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113038 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Karen_Lucas_2021_Fellow-e1617052119338.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Karen_Lucas_2021_Fellow-e1617052119338.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Karen_Lucas_2021_Fellow-e1617052119338.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Karen_Lucas_2021_Fellow-e1617052119338.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Karen_Lucas_2021_Fellow-e1617052119338.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Karen_Lucas_2021_Fellow-e1617052119338.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Karen_Lucas_2021_Fellow-e1617052119338.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Karen_Lucas_2021_Fellow-e1617052119338.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /><br />\n<strong>Kaz</strong><br />\n<em>Sex educator + podcaster | Kenya</em><br />\nEducator building a positive and safe space for sexual discourse in Kenya through her podcast and TV segment <em>The Spread</em>. Through these platforms, Kaz illuminates and confronts the pleasure gap, challenges restrictive LGBTQ+ policy and emphasizes reproductive rights.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113025 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Francisca_Mutapi_2021_Fellow-e1617051552579.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Francisca_Mutapi_2021_Fellow-e1617051552579.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Francisca_Mutapi_2021_Fellow-e1617051552579.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Francisca_Mutapi_2021_Fellow-e1617051552579.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Francisca_Mutapi_2021_Fellow-e1617051552579.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Francisca_Mutapi_2021_Fellow-e1617051552579.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Francisca_Mutapi_2021_Fellow-e1617051552579.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Francisca_Mutapi_2021_Fellow-e1617051552579.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /><br />\n<strong>Francisca Mutapi</strong><br />\n<em>Epidemiologist | Zimbabwe + UK</em><br />\nPan-African biomedical researcher empowering African scientists and policymakers to tackle infectious diseases and improve epidemic preparedness. Francisca Mutapi leads collaborative research developing and deploying infectious disease diagnostic tools and interventions across the continent, especially in places with limited infrastructure or resources.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113026 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mavis_Nduchwa_2021_Fellow-e1617051608156.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mavis_Nduchwa_2021_Fellow-e1617051608156.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mavis_Nduchwa_2021_Fellow-e1617051608156.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mavis_Nduchwa_2021_Fellow-e1617051608156.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mavis_Nduchwa_2021_Fellow-e1617051608156.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mavis_Nduchwa_2021_Fellow-e1617051608156.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mavis_Nduchwa_2021_Fellow-e1617051608156.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mavis_Nduchwa_2021_Fellow-e1617051608156.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /><br />\n<strong>Mavis Nduchwa</strong><br />\n<em>Honey aggregator | Botswana</em><br />\nFounder of Kalahari Honey, which uses beehives as &#8220;living fences&#8221; to mitigate conflict between Botswana&#8217;s farmers and foraging elephants, who are afraid of bees. This local form of conservation, based on traditional knowledge and practices, also provides income to the farmers through honey sales.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113027 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Tom_Lee_Osborn_2021_Fellow-e1617051658453.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Tom_Lee_Osborn_2021_Fellow-e1617051658453.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Tom_Lee_Osborn_2021_Fellow-e1617051658453.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Tom_Lee_Osborn_2021_Fellow-e1617051658453.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Tom_Lee_Osborn_2021_Fellow-e1617051658453.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Tom_Lee_Osborn_2021_Fellow-e1617051658453.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Tom_Lee_Osborn_2021_Fellow-e1617051658453.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Tom_Lee_Osborn_2021_Fellow-e1617051658453.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /><br />\n<strong>Tom Osborn</strong><br />\n<em>Mental health innovator | Kenya</em><br />\nFounder of Shamiri, a youth-led organization providing mental health care solutions to teens across Kenya, where 45 percent of young people report clinical depression. In a region where mental health professionals are scarce and disorders are stigmatized, Shamiri implements evidence-based, low-cost wellness interventions in Kenyan schools.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_113050\" style=\"width: 910px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-113050\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-full wp-image-113050\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali-Prasad-RangerRanger_Arunachal.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"900\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali-Prasad-RangerRanger_Arunachal.jpg 5616w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali-Prasad-RangerRanger_Arunachal.jpg?resize=150,100 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali-Prasad-RangerRanger_Arunachal.jpg?resize=250,167 250w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali-Prasad-RangerRanger_Arunachal.jpg?resize=768,512 768w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali-Prasad-RangerRanger_Arunachal.jpg?resize=530,353 530w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali-Prasad-RangerRanger_Arunachal.jpg?resize=1536,1024 1536w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali-Prasad-RangerRanger_Arunachal.jpg?resize=2048,1365 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-113050\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">The hornbill bird beak is traditionally used to adorn the headgear of the Nyishi tribe in Arunachal Pradesh, India. In this image, a forest guard holds an artificial replacement, part of a conservation effort to save the iconic birds documented in journalist Sonali Prasad&#8217;s <em>Ranger Ranger</em> series, chronicling the guardians of India&#8217;s national parks.</p></div>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113028 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali_Prasad_2021_Fellow-e1617051716184.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali_Prasad_2021_Fellow-e1617051716184.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali_Prasad_2021_Fellow-e1617051716184.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali_Prasad_2021_Fellow-e1617051716184.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali_Prasad_2021_Fellow-e1617051716184.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali_Prasad_2021_Fellow-e1617051716184.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali_Prasad_2021_Fellow-e1617051716184.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sonali_Prasad_2021_Fellow-e1617051716184.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Sonali Prasad</strong><br />\n<em>Environmental journalist + artist | India</em><br />\nArtist and journalist documenting the emotional grief and human toll of climate change in order to inspire people to take action. Sonali Prasad&#8217;s work tells stories about loss, survival and resilience in response to environmental crises and natural disasters. She establishes new rituals and practices to help us mourn a world stricken by catastrophic climate events.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113030 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sathya_Raghu_2021_Fellow-e1617051812779.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sathya_Raghu_2021_Fellow-e1617051812779.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sathya_Raghu_2021_Fellow-e1617051812779.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sathya_Raghu_2021_Fellow-e1617051812779.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sathya_Raghu_2021_Fellow-e1617051812779.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sathya_Raghu_2021_Fellow-e1617051812779.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sathya_Raghu_2021_Fellow-e1617051812779.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Sathya_Raghu_2021_Fellow-e1617051812779.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /><br />\n<strong>Sathya Raghu</strong><br />\n<em>Green farming innovator | India</em><br />\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Green farming entrepreneur helping small-holder farmers in India confront the impacts and crises of climate change. Sathya Raghu cofounded Kheyti, an agricultural startup building low-cost greenhouse systems that protect crops from climate risks, such as extreme heat and water shortages, and radically improve yields.</span></p>\n<hr />\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113031 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Nithya_Ramanathan_2021_Fellow-e1617051846633.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Nithya_Ramanathan_2021_Fellow-e1617051846633.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Nithya_Ramanathan_2021_Fellow-e1617051846633.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Nithya_Ramanathan_2021_Fellow-e1617051846633.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Nithya_Ramanathan_2021_Fellow-e1617051846633.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Nithya_Ramanathan_2021_Fellow-e1617051846633.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Nithya_Ramanathan_2021_Fellow-e1617051846633.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Nithya_Ramanathan_2021_Fellow-e1617051846633.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /><br />\n<strong>Nithya Ramanathan</strong><br />\n<em>Technologist | US</em><br />\nFounder and CEO of Nexleaf, a nonprofit using data and technology to improve the health of people around the world. Nexleaf partners with countries to create data analytic tools to keep vaccines at the correct temperature and alert local staff when vaccines are in danger of becoming unusable.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113032 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Fariel_Salahuddin_2021_Fellow-e1617051879752.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Fariel_Salahuddin_2021_Fellow-e1617051879752.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Fariel_Salahuddin_2021_Fellow-e1617051879752.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Fariel_Salahuddin_2021_Fellow-e1617051879752.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Fariel_Salahuddin_2021_Fellow-e1617051879752.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Fariel_Salahuddin_2021_Fellow-e1617051879752.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Fariel_Salahuddin_2021_Fellow-e1617051879752.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Fariel_Salahuddin_2021_Fellow-e1617051879752.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /></p>\n<p><strong><br />\nFariel Salahuddin</strong><br />\n<em>Barter economist | Pakistan</em><br />\nFinance expert and founder of UpTrade, a company helping Pakistani herding communities use their livestock to acquire civic-improvement assets (like water pumps and solar lights) instead of cash. Fariel Salahuddin aims to make livestock bartering as common as micro-finance in order to provide farmers higher value for their assets, relieve onerous debt, eliminate the need for charity funding and build self-reliance.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_113062\" style=\"width: 910px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-113062\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-full wp-image-113062\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán-Santillán-IMG_8700.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"900\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán-Santillán-IMG_8700.jpg 5184w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán-Santillán-IMG_8700.jpg?resize=150,100 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán-Santillán-IMG_8700.jpg?resize=250,167 250w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán-Santillán-IMG_8700.jpg?resize=768,512 768w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán-Santillán-IMG_8700.jpg?resize=530,353 530w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán-Santillán-IMG_8700.jpg?resize=1536,1024 1536w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán-Santillán-IMG_8700.jpg?resize=2048,1365 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-113062\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Born and raised in the Oaxacan region of Mixteca Baja, one of Mexico&#8217;s culturally rich but economically poor regions, Germán Santillán cofounded Oaxacanita Chocolate to help revitalize the economy of his homeland through a neglected indigenous crop: cocoa.</p></div>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113033 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán_Santillán_2021_Fellow-e1617051913638.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán_Santillán_2021_Fellow-e1617051913638.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán_Santillán_2021_Fellow-e1617051913638.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán_Santillán_2021_Fellow-e1617051913638.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán_Santillán_2021_Fellow-e1617051913638.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán_Santillán_2021_Fellow-e1617051913638.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán_Santillán_2021_Fellow-e1617051913638.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Germán_Santillán_2021_Fellow-e1617051913638.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /></p>\n<p><strong><br />\nGermán Santillán</strong><br />\n<em>Cultural chocolatier | Mexico</em><br />\nFounder of Oaxacanita Chocolate, an artisanal chocolate company reviving indigenous Mixtec chocolate-making practices and craft. Drawing on Oaxaca&#8217;s rich history as the cradle of chocolate, the company partners with indigenous communities to spark economic growth in one of Mexico&#8217;s culturally rich but economically poor regions.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113034 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Keenan_Scott_II_2021_Fellow-e1617051959945.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Keenan_Scott_II_2021_Fellow-e1617051959945.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Keenan_Scott_II_2021_Fellow-e1617051959945.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Keenan_Scott_II_2021_Fellow-e1617051959945.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Keenan_Scott_II_2021_Fellow-e1617051959945.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Keenan_Scott_II_2021_Fellow-e1617051959945.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Keenan_Scott_II_2021_Fellow-e1617051959945.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Keenan_Scott_II_2021_Fellow-e1617051959945.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /><br />\n<strong>Keenan Scott II</strong><br />\n<em>Theater artist | US</em><br />\nPlaywright and actor combining spoken word, slam poetry and song into theater works that celebrate all aspects of the African Diaspora. Keenan Scott II&#8217;s play <em>Thoughts of a Colored Man</em>, slated to premiere on Broadway, follows seven Black men as they confront the highs and lows in their communities and invites the audience to bear witness to their emotional lives.</p>\n<hr />\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113035 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Smita_Sharma_2021_Fellow-e1617051989177.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Smita_Sharma_2021_Fellow-e1617051989177.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Smita_Sharma_2021_Fellow-e1617051989177.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Smita_Sharma_2021_Fellow-e1617051989177.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Smita_Sharma_2021_Fellow-e1617051989177.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Smita_Sharma_2021_Fellow-e1617051989177.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Smita_Sharma_2021_Fellow-e1617051989177.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Smita_Sharma_2021_Fellow-e1617051989177.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /><br />\n<strong>Smita Sharma</strong><br />\n<em>Photojournalist | India</em><br />\nPhotojournalist documenting victims of gender-based violence, sexual crimes and human trafficking in the Global South through long-form visual narratives. Smita Sharma uses visceral and beautiful images to bring her subjects out of the world of faceless statistics and emphasize their humanity.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_113053\" style=\"width: 910px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-113053\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"size-full wp-image-113053\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/mila-turajlic-Mila-archive-scanning.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"900\" height=\"507\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/mila-turajlic-Mila-archive-scanning.jpeg 1424w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/mila-turajlic-Mila-archive-scanning.jpeg?resize=150,84 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/mila-turajlic-Mila-archive-scanning.jpeg?resize=250,141 250w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/mila-turajlic-Mila-archive-scanning.jpeg?resize=768,433 768w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/mila-turajlic-Mila-archive-scanning.jpeg?resize=530,298 530w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/mila-turajlic-Mila-archive-scanning.jpeg?resize=283,160 283w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/mila-turajlic-Mila-archive-scanning.jpeg?resize=185,104 185w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/mila-turajlic-Mila-archive-scanning.jpeg?resize=73,42 73w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" /><p id=\"caption-attachment-113053\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Filmmaker Mila Turajlic reviews unedited footage for her latest project based on the Non-Aligned Movement Archive. Shot by a now-deceased Yugoslavian cameraman, the rare footage documents the African Independence Movements of the 20th century close up.</p></div>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" class=\"alignleft wp-image-113036 size-full\" src=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mila_Turajlic_2021_Fellow-e1617052022638.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mila_Turajlic_2021_Fellow-e1617052022638.jpg 200w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mila_Turajlic_2021_Fellow-e1617052022638.jpg?resize=150,150 150w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mila_Turajlic_2021_Fellow-e1617052022638.jpg?resize=32,32 32w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mila_Turajlic_2021_Fellow-e1617052022638.jpg?resize=50,50 50w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mila_Turajlic_2021_Fellow-e1617052022638.jpg?resize=64,64 64w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mila_Turajlic_2021_Fellow-e1617052022638.jpg?resize=96,96 96w, https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/Mila_Turajlic_2021_Fellow-e1617052022638.jpg?resize=128,128 128w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 200px) 100vw, 200px\" /><br />\n<strong>Mila Turajlić</strong><br />\n<em>Documentary filmmaker | Serbia</em><br />\nFilmmaker from the former Yugoslavia awakening forgotten personal histories to create new forms of political imagination. By amplifying the voices and experiences buried in the collapse of her country, Mila Turajlić seeks to bridge gaps between estranged neighbors and heal the wounds of societies that have come undone.</p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>The TED Fellows program is thrilled to announce the 2021 cohort of TED Fellows, whose work spans five continents and represents 14 countries &#8212; including, for the first time, Peru. Each TED Fellow was selected for their remarkable achievements, the potential impact of their work and their commitment to community building. This year&#8217;s TED Fellows <a class=\"read-more\" title=\"Read more\" href=\"https://blog.ted.com/meet-the-2021-class-of-ted-fellows/\">[<span>&hellip;</span>]</a></p>\n","protected":false},"author":15335046,"featured_media":113005,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"amp_status":"","spay_email":""},"categories":[562301618],"tags":[37208,562301617,562301665],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"https://blog.ted.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2021/03/TED015-TED-2021_TED-Blog-870x653-01.png","_links":{"self":[{"href":"https://blog.ted.com/wp-json/wp/v2/posts/112991"}],"collection":[{"href":"https://blog.ted.com/wp-json/wp/v2/pos